Cedric Richmond, Senior Advisor to the President and Director of the White House Office of Public Engagement, hosted a meeting with the Circle of Protection, a coalition of Christian denominations, to discuss President Biden's Build Back Better agenda. The meeting aimed to gather feedback on the agenda's impact on communities. The faith leaders emphasized the importance of including the Child Tax Credit, Earned Income Tax Credit, and housing support in the bill. They also highlighted the need for legislation that promotes racial equity and economic mobility for all backgrounds. Administration officials reaffirmed the President's commitment to creating jobs, lifting children out of poverty, and lowering costs for working families. They emphasized that these initiatives would be funded by making the tax code fairer and ensuring that the wealthiest individuals and corporations pay their fair share. The Administration also expressed its dedication to racial equity and economic opportunity, and promised continued engagement and partnership with the Circle of Protection.